column1:
Perform a multiphase computed tomography (CT) scan in trauma patients with:
• 
visible haematuria;
• 
non-visible haematuria and one episode of hypotension;
• 
a history of rapid deceleration injury and/or significant associated injuries;
• 
penetrating trauma;
• 
clinical signs suggesting renal trauma e.g. flank pain, abrasions, fractured ribs, 
abdominal distension and/or a mass and tenderness.
